File: Fitch warns that banks will face multiple challenges like a decline in client activity and lower interest rates. JOHANNESBURG - Credit ratings agency, Fitch has downgraded five of South Africa’s banks to BB negative outlook. Absa, FirstRand Bank Limited, Investec, Nedbank and Standard Bank are all affected. READ: Moody's move SA to junk status This is mainly due to the impact the COVID-19 pandemic has on operating environment and key financial metrics. Fitch warns that banks will face multiple challenges like a decline in client activity and lower interest rates.